    "   \"id\": \"m001\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Influencer Campaign ROI Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Project Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"This notebook analyzes influencer marketing campaign results across creators, platforms, and campaigns. We measure engagement, conversions, customer acquisition cost (CAC), and return on spend to determine which partnerships are truly driving business value.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Learning Objectives\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Evaluate influencer campaigns using business-relevant metrics: CAC, ROI, conversion rate.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Compare performance across influencer tiers (nano, micro, macro, mega).\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Assess platform effectiveness for influencer marketing.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Identify high-ROI and low-ROI campaigns with actionable explanations.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Practice ROI analysis with realistic marketing data.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Business / Research Problem\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Brands spend significant budgets on influencer partnerships but often lack rigorous performance tracking beyond vanity metrics (likes, followers). This analysis focuses on conversion-level and cost-level metrics to evaluate true ROI.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Why This Analysis Matters\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Influencer marketing budgets are growing, but ROI measurement remains weak in most organizations. A data-driven approach helps allocate spend toward partnerships that generate actual conversions, not just impressions.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m002\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Synthetic dataset of **500 influencer campaign entries** with:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `campaign_id`, `influencer_id`, `influencer_name`\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `platform` — Instagram, YouTube, TikTok, Twitter/X\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `influencer_tier` — Nano (<10K), Micro (10-100K), Macro (100K-1M), Mega (1M+)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `campaign_spend` — dollars paid to the influencer\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `impressions`, `engagements`, `clicks`, `conversions`\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `revenue_generated` — attributed revenue\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Source and License Notes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Synthetically generated for educational purposes. No external download needed.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m003\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Environment Setup\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c001\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for pkg in [\\\"pandas\\\", \\\"numpy\\\", \\\"matplotlib\\\", \\\"seaborn\\\", \\\"scipy\\\"]:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        importlib.import_module(pkg)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    except ImportError:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        subprocess.check_call([sys.executable, \\\"-m\\\", \\\"pip\\\", \\\"install\\\", \\\"-q\\\", pkg])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Environment ready.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m004\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Imports\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c002\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import numpy as np\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import pandas as pd\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import seaborn as sns\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from scipy import stats\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import warnings\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"warnings.filterwarnings(\\\"ignore\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.set_style(\\\"whitegrid\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"%matplotlib inline\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m005\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Configuration / Constants\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c003\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"SEED = 42\\n\",\n",
    "    \"N_CAMPAIGNS = 500\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"PLATFORMS = [\\\"Instagram\\\", \\\"YouTube\\\", \\\"TikTok\\\", \\\"Twitter/X\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"TIERS = [\\\"Nano\\\", \\\"Micro\\\", \\\"Macro\\\", \\\"Mega\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"TIER_PROFILES = {\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"Nano\\\":  {\\\"spend_range\\\": (200, 1500),   \\\"imp_range\\\": (5000, 30000),   \\\"eng_rate\\\": 0.06, \\\"cvr\\\": 0.025},\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"Micro\\\": {\\\"spend_range\\\": (1000, 8000),  \\\"imp_range\\\": (20000, 150000),  \\\"eng_rate\\\": 0.045, \\\"cvr\\\": 0.018},\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"Macro\\\": {\\\"spend_range\\\": (5000, 30000), \\\"imp_range\\\": (100000, 800000), \\\"eng_rate\\\": 0.03, \\\"cvr\\\": 0.012},\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"Mega\\\":  {\\\"spend_range\\\": (20000, 100000),\\\"imp_range\\\": (500000, 5000000),\\\"eng_rate\\\": 0.02, \\\"cvr\\\": 0.008},\\n\",\n",
    "    \"}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Configuration loaded.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m006\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Generation\\n\",\n",
    "    \"We create realistic influencer campaign data where nano/micro influencers have higher engagement rates but lower reach, while mega influencers have huge reach but lower conversion efficiency.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c004\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"rng = np.random.default_rng(SEED)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"rows = []\\n\",\n",
    "    \"influencer_names = [f\\\"Creator_{i:03d}\\\" for i in range(1, 151)]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for i in range(N_CAMPAIGNS):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    tier = rng.choice(TIERS, p=[0.30, 0.35, 0.25, 0.10])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    profile = TIER_PROFILES[tier]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    platform = rng.choice(PLATFORMS, p=[0.35, 0.25, 0.25, 0.15])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    influencer = rng.choice(influencer_names[:30] if tier == \\\"Nano\\\" else\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                            influencer_names[30:70] if tier == \\\"Micro\\\" else\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                            influencer_names[70:120] if tier == \\\"Macro\\\" else\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                            influencer_names[120:])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    spend = rng.uniform(*profile[\\\"spend_range\\\"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    impressions = max(1000, int(rng.uniform(*profile[\\\"imp_range\\\"])))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    eng_rate = np.clip(rng.normal(profile[\\\"eng_rate\\\"], 0.015), 0.005, 0.15)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    engagements = max(1, int(impressions * eng_rate))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    click_rate = rng.uniform(0.01, 0.05)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    clicks = max(0, int(impressions * click_rate))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    cvr = np.clip(rng.normal(profile[\\\"cvr\\\"], 0.008), 0.001, 0.08)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    conversions = max(0, int(clicks * cvr))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    avg_order = rng.uniform(30, 120)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    revenue = conversions * avg_order\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    rows.append({\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"campaign_id\\\": f\\\"C{i+1:04d}\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"influencer_name\\\": influencer,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"platform\\\": platform,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"influencer_tier\\\": tier,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"campaign_spend\\\": round(spend, 2),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"impressions\\\": impressions,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"engagements\\\": engagements,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"clicks\\\": clicks,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"conversions\\\": conversions,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"revenue_generated\\\": round(revenue, 2),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    })\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df = pd.DataFrame(rows)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"engagement_rate\\\"] = df[\\\"engagements\\\"] / df[\\\"impressions\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"ctr\\\"] = df[\\\"clicks\\\"] / df[\\\"impressions\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"cac\\\"] = np.where(df[\\\"conversions\\\"] > 0, df[\\\"campaign_spend\\\"] / df[\\\"conversions\\\"], np.nan)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"roi\\\"] = np.where(df[\\\"campaign_spend\\\"] > 0, (df[\\\"revenue_generated\\\"] - df[\\\"campaign_spend\\\"]) / df[\\\"campaign_spend\\\"], np.nan)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Dataset shape: {df.shape}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df.head()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m007\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Data Validation Checks\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c005\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Missing values:\\\\n{df.isnull().sum()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"\\\\nNegative spend: {(df['campaign_spend'] < 0).sum()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Negative impressions: {(df['impressions'] < 0).sum()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Conversions > clicks: {(df['conversions'] > df['clicks']).sum()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Campaigns with 0 conversions: {(df['conversions'] == 0).sum()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"\\\\n✅ Validation passed.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m008\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Data Cleaning\\n\",\n",
    "    \"The dataset is clean by construction. In real scenarios, you would:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Verify attribution windows (last-click vs multi-touch)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Remove test/internal campaigns\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Handle multi-post campaigns by aggregation\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m009\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Exploratory Data Analysis\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c006\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Total campaigns: {len(df)}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Total spend: ${df['campaign_spend'].sum():,.0f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Total revenue: ${df['revenue_generated'].sum():,.0f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Overall ROI: {(df['revenue_generated'].sum() - df['campaign_spend'].sum()) / df['campaign_spend'].sum():.1%}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Avg engagement rate: {df['engagement_rate'].mean():.2%}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Campaigns with conversions: {(df['conversions'] > 0).sum()} / {len(df)}\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m010\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Univariate Analysis\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c007\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(16, 4))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].hist(df[\\\"campaign_spend\\\"], bins=40, color=\\\"steelblue\\\", edgecolor=\\\"white\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_title(\\\"Campaign Spend Distribution\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_xlabel(\\\"Spend ($)\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"valid_roi = df[\\\"roi\\\"].dropna()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].hist(valid_roi.clip(-1, 5), bins=40, color=\\\"seagreen\\\", edgecolor=\\\"white\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_title(\\\"ROI Distribution (clipped [-1, 5])\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].axvline(0, color=\\\"red\\\", ls=\\\"--\\\", label=\\\"Break-even\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].legend()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[2].hist(df[\\\"engagement_rate\\\"], bins=40, color=\\\"coral\\\", edgecolor=\\\"white\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[2].set_title(\\\"Engagement Rate Distribution\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m011\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Bivariate / Multivariate Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### ROI and CAC by influencer tier\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c008\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"tier_summary = df.groupby(\\\"influencer_tier\\\").agg(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    campaigns=(\\\"campaign_id\\\", \\\"count\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    total_spend=(\\\"campaign_spend\\\", \\\"sum\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    total_revenue=(\\\"revenue_generated\\\", \\\"sum\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    avg_engagement_rate=(\\\"engagement_rate\\\", \\\"mean\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    avg_conversions=(\\\"conversions\\\", \\\"mean\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    median_cac=(\\\"cac\\\", \\\"median\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    median_roi=(\\\"roi\\\", \\\"median\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \").reindex(TIERS)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"tier_summary[\\\"overall_roi\\\"] = (tier_summary[\\\"total_revenue\\\"] - tier_summary[\\\"total_spend\\\"]) / tier_summary[\\\"total_spend\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"=== Performance by Influencer Tier ===\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"tier_summary\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c009\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(16, 5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"tier_order = TIERS\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.boxplot(data=df, x=\\\"influencer_tier\\\", y=\\\"engagement_rate\\\", order=tier_order, ax=axes[0], palette=\\\"Set2\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_title(\\\"Engagement Rate by Tier\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"valid_cac = df.dropna(subset=[\\\"cac\\\"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.boxplot(data=valid_cac, x=\\\"influencer_tier\\\", y=\\\"cac\\\", order=tier_order, ax=axes[1], palette=\\\"Set3\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_title(\\\"CAC by Tier\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_ylim(0, valid_cac[\\\"cac\\\"].quantile(0.95))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.boxplot(data=df, x=\\\"influencer_tier\\\", y=\\\"roi\\\", order=tier_order, ax=axes[2], palette=\\\"pastel\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[2].set_title(\\\"ROI by Tier\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[2].set_ylim(-1.5, df[\\\"roi\\\"].quantile(0.95))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[2].axhline(0, color=\\\"red\\\", ls=\\\"--\\\", alpha=0.5)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
