    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"plat_summary = df.groupby(\\\"platform\\\").agg(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    campaigns=(\\\"campaign_id\\\", \\\"count\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    total_spend=(\\\"campaign_spend\\\", \\\"sum\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    total_revenue=(\\\"revenue_generated\\\", \\\"sum\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    avg_eng_rate=(\\\"engagement_rate\\\", \\\"mean\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    median_roi=(\\\"roi\\\", \\\"median\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \").sort_values(\\\"median_roi\\\", ascending=False)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plat_summary[\\\"overall_roi\\\"] = (plat_summary[\\\"total_revenue\\\"] - plat_summary[\\\"total_spend\\\"]) / plat_summary[\\\"total_spend\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plat_summary\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m013\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Feature-Specific Insights\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Top and bottom performing influencers\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c011\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"inf_perf = df.groupby(\\\"influencer_name\\\").agg(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    campaigns=(\\\"campaign_id\\\", \\\"count\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    total_spend=(\\\"campaign_spend\\\", \\\"sum\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    total_revenue=(\\\"revenue_generated\\\", \\\"sum\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    total_conversions=(\\\"conversions\\\", \\\"sum\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \").query(\\\"campaigns >= 3\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"inf_perf[\\\"roi\\\"] = (inf_perf[\\\"total_revenue\\\"] - inf_perf[\\\"total_spend\\\"]) / inf_perf[\\\"total_spend\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"inf_perf[\\\"cac\\\"] = np.where(inf_perf[\\\"total_conversions\\\"] > 0, inf_perf[\\\"total_spend\\\"] / inf_perf[\\\"total_conversions\\\"], np.nan)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"=== Top 10 Influencers by ROI (min 3 campaigns) ===\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(inf_perf.sort_values(\\\"roi\\\", ascending=False).head(10)[[\\\"campaigns\\\", \\\"total_spend\\\", \\\"total_revenue\\\", \\\"roi\\\", \\\"cac\\\"]])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"\\\\n=== Bottom 10 Influencers by ROI ===\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(inf_perf.sort_values(\\\"roi\\\").head(10)[[\\\"campaigns\\\", \\\"total_spend\\\", \\\"total_revenue\\\", \\\"roi\\\", \\\"cac\\\"]])\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m014\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Statistical Checks\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Is nano/micro ROI significantly better than macro/mega?\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c012\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"small = df[df[\\\"influencer_tier\\\"].isin([\\\"Nano\\\", \\\"Micro\\\"])][\\\"roi\\\"].dropna()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"large = df[df[\\\"influencer_tier\\\"].isin([\\\"Macro\\\", \\\"Mega\\\"])][\\\"roi\\\"].dropna()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"stat, p = stats.mannwhitneyu(small, large, alternative=\\\"greater\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Small influencers (Nano+Micro) median ROI: {small.median():.2f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Large influencers (Macro+Mega) median ROI: {large.median():.2f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Mann-Whitney U: stat={stat:.1f}, p={p:.4f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Result: {'Significant' if p < 0.05 else 'Not significant'} at α=0.05\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m015\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Visual Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Spend vs Revenue scatter by tier\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c013\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 7))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"colors = {\\\"Nano\\\": \\\"#2ecc71\\\", \\\"Micro\\\": \\\"#3498db\\\", \\\"Macro\\\": \\\"#e67e22\\\", \\\"Mega\\\": \\\"#e74c3c\\\"}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for tier in TIERS:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    subset = df[df[\\\"influencer_tier\\\"] == tier]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    ax.scatter(subset[\\\"campaign_spend\\\"], subset[\\\"revenue_generated\\\"],\\n\",\n",
    "    \"              alpha=0.5, label=tier, color=colors[tier], s=30)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"max_val = max(df[\\\"campaign_spend\\\"].max(), df[\\\"revenue_generated\\\"].max())\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.plot([0, max_val], [0, max_val], \\\"k--\\\", alpha=0.3, label=\\\"Break-even line\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_xlabel(\\\"Campaign Spend ($)\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_ylabel(\\\"Revenue Generated ($)\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_title(\\\"Spend vs Revenue by Influencer Tier\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.legend()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m016\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Key Findings\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Nano and micro influencers deliver higher engagement rates and often better ROI per dollar spent** compared to macro and mega influencers.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Mega influencers drive volume (impressions) but with lower efficiency.** Their high absolute spend means poor-performing campaigns are costly.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Many campaigns produce zero conversions,** especially at higher spend tiers — highlighting the importance of pre-screening influencer audience quality.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Platform performance varies,** but the differences are secondary to influencer selection quality.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **CAC for nano influencers tends to be lower,** making them attractive for performance-oriented campaigns with limited budgets.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m017\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Limitations\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Synthetic data; real influencer marketing has highly variable attribution quality.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Attribution is modeled as direct, but real campaigns involve assisted conversions.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- No brand awareness or long-term value tracking.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- No audience overlap analysis between influencers.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Content quality and brand fit are not measured.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m018\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Recommendations / Next Steps\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Shift budget toward nano/micro influencers** for performance campaigns.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Use mega influencers for brand awareness goals,** not direct conversion.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Track audience overlap** to avoid paying multiple influencers reaching the same users.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Implement minimum conversion thresholds** before renewing influencer contracts.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **A/B test content briefs** to isolate what type of creative drives the most conversions.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"6. **Build long-term relationships** with top-ROI creators rather than one-off sponsorships.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m019\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Common Mistakes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Evaluating influencers by follower count alone.** Engagement rate and conversion rate matter far more.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Not separating brand awareness from conversion campaigns.** The metrics for each are completely different.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Ignoring CAC.** A campaign with 100 conversions but $50K spend may be worse than 20 conversions at $2K.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Not accounting for fake followers/engagement.** Audit engagement authenticity before partnering.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Measuring ROI too early.** Some influencer campaigns have delayed conversion effects that attribution windows miss.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m020\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Mini Challenge / Exercises\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Build a cost-efficiency quadrant chart** with axes: engagement rate (x) and ROI (y). Label each quadrant.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Calculate the \\\"break-even\\\" conversion count** each campaign needs given its spend and assumed AOV.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Create an influencer scorecard** ranking creators by a composite of ROI, engagement rate, and consistency.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Simulate doubling budget on top-10 ROI influencers.** What would the projected revenue be?\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Add a time dimension** and study whether influencer performance degrades with repeat campaigns.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m021\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Final Summary / Key Takeaways\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Smaller influencers often deliver better cost efficiency** — higher engagement rates and lower CAC.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **ROI should be the primary evaluation metric,** not impressions or engagement alone.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Many campaigns fail to generate any conversions.** Pre-campaign audience quality checks are essential.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Platform choice matters less than influencer quality.** Focus on creator selection over platform allocation.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Influencer marketing ROI analysis requires proper attribution** — invest in tracking infrastructure before scaling spend.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  }\n",
    " ],\n",
